property_value: UBPROP:0000008 "Compared to terrestial animals, the cornea of zebrafish is relatively flat. It consists of nonpigmented, stratified squamous nonkeratinizing epithelial cells, attached to a thick basement membrane that is considered to be analogous to the Bowman's membrane in mammals. In fish, and aquatic vertebrates in general, the cornea plays no role in focusing light, since it has virtually the same refractive index as water" xsd:string

[Term]
id: UBERON:0000965
name: lens of camera-type eye
namespace: uberon
def: "A transparent and refractive lens located posterior to the iris. The lens of camera-type eye refracts light to be focused on the retina." [http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165, Wikipedia:Lens_(anatomy)]
comment: The lens is avascular and nourished by diffusion from the aqueous and vitreous humors.
