property_value: UBPROP:0000007 "facial" xsd:string
property_value: UBPROP:0000011 "The face develops from outward growth of tissue located rostral to the cranium & pharynx. The lower jaw and most of the upper jaw are formed by growth of the first pharyngeal (branchial) arch. The upper incisor region and the nose and forehead (frontal region) are formed from tissue located rostral to the neural tube (frontonasal prominence)" xsd:string {source="vanat.cvm.umn.edu/TFFlectPDFs/LectFaceDevelop.pdf"}

